    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 11 March 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He has just received Oláh’s letters. Francesco II Sforza thanks him for
                            the thorough report. They have heard that the Anabaptist plague is
                            spreading in Antwerp. King Frederick II is marrying Dorothea of Denmark.
                            The Emperor is planning to go to Italy, and Andrea Doria is about to set
                            out for Baradino at his order. The Pope tends to side with the French,
                            but this does not matter. The prince has written to the Queen in detail
                            about what they have heard about Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha, and the
                            events that have taken place in Rome and Spain. The Italian sword Oláh
                            is getting is, simply put, a masterpiece.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p>Quae XXI. item XXII. praeteriti exarasti, pridie accepi.<note
                        type="critic">We do not know these letters.</note>
                    <persName>Princeps</persName><note type="critic">Francesco II Sforza.</note>
                    meus tibi gratias agit, quod tam diligenter operam tuam in scriptione praestes
                    et te rogat, ut in ea assidue verseris. Audivimus Antverpienses laborare
                    pestilentia Anabaptistica; si verum est, fac, ut sciam. Dux
                        <persName>Fridericus</persName><note type="critic">Frederick II, Elector
                        Palatine of the Rhine.</note> uxorem ducet illustrissimam
                        <persName>Dorotheam</persName>,<note type="critic">Dorothea of Denmark
                        married Frederick II, Elector Palatine of the Rhine in Brussels on 18 May,
                        1535.</note> hoc enim ex litteris caesaris ad principem meum iamdiu
                    audivimus. Caesar transmittet in Italia, classis paratur. <persName>Princeps
                        Auria</persName><note type="critic">Andrea Doria.</note> cum XV triremibus
                    brevi profecturus est <placeName>Baradino</placeName>, nam caesare ita iubente.
                        <persName>Pontifex</persName> in Gallicas partes inclinat, sed parum de eo
                    timendum est, non enim hiscere audebit. Quae de
                        <persName>Aenobarbo</persName><note type="critic">Hayreddin Barbarossa
                        Pasha.</note> nuper intelleximus, item urbana nova et Hispanica,
                        <persName>dux</persName> serenissimae reginae uberrime scribit. Ensem
                        Italicum<note type="critic">See Ep.
                        528.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15350209_1</ref> habebis brevi affabre factum.
                    Haec scripsi temporibus exclusus, tu veniam mihi dabis, si longiori epistola non
                    utar. Vale et <persName>Scepperum</persName><note type="critic">Cornelis de
                        Schepper.</note> saluta meo nomine. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XI. Martii anno MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
